==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Samiel
<hw>Sa"mi*el</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Turk.
<ets>sam-yeli</ets>; Ar. <ets>samm</ets> poison + Turk. <ets>yel</ets>
wind. Cf. <er>Simoom</er>.]</ety> <def>A hot and destructive wind that
sometimes blows, in Turkey, from the desert. It is identical with the
<altname>simoom</altname> of Arabia and the <altname>kamsin</altname> of
Syria.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Samiot</ent>⟦br⟧
